n Dibley]], both in 1976.\n\nHe also lost a final to Spanish US Open winner and French Open finalist, [[Manuel Orantes]].\n\nHe also won 3 doubles titles, one at Oslo in 1974, North Conway in 1975 and Little Rock in 1978. Success was also seen in the men's doubles where he made it to the quarter finals of the US Open, the third round of Wimbledon, and the second round of the French Open.<ref>{{cite web| title=Haroon Rahim|url=http://www.daviscup.com/en/players/player/profile.aspx?playerid=10002757 |accessdate=1 December 2012}}</ref>\n \nHaroon Rahim is the winner of the closest match ever played, he beat Tom Gorman 6\u20137<sup>(3\u20135)</sup>, 7\u20136<sup>(5\u20131)</sup>, 7\u20136<sup>(5\u20134)</sup> Pennsylvania Grass Championships, as both players never losing their serve, each set went to a tie break with Haroon winning the match by just one point.\n\nLast known to be in the US, Haroon retired from tennis, severed contact with his family and his whereabouts are unknown.<ref>{{cite web| title=Crazy Diamonds|url=http://dawn.com/2012/11/01/crazy-diamonds |accessdate=1 December 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Grand Slams performance timelines==\n\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#efefef\"\n! Tournament !! 1977 !! 1976 !! 1975 !! 1971\n|-\n|[[Australian Open]]\n|align=\"center\"|-\n|align=\"center\"|-\n|align=\"center\"|-\n|align=\"center\"|-\n|-\n|[[French Open]]\n|align=\"center\"|-\n|align=\"center\"|-\n|align=\"center\" style=\"background:#afeeee;\"|2R\n|align=\"center\"|-\n|-\n|[[Wimbledon Championships|Wimbledon]]\n|align=\"center\" style=\"background:#afeeee;\"|2R\n|align=\"center\" style=\"background:#afeeee;\"|2R\n|align=\"center\"|-\n|align=\"center\"|-\n|-\n|[[U.S. Open (tennis)|US Open]]\n|align=\"center\"|-\n|align=\"center\"|-\n|align=\"center\"|-\n|align=\"center\" style=\"background:#afeeee;\"|3R\n|-\n|}\n\n===Doubles===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#efefef\"\n! Tournament !! 1976 !! 1972 !! 1971\n|-\n|[[Australian Open]]\n|align=\"